So last digits: 0,2,4,6,8 — all even, as expected.

Frequencies:
- 0: 200, 140? No — 140 ends in 0? Yes — 140 and 200 → two 0s
- 2: 124, 182 → two
- 4: 174, 134, 140? 140 ends in 0 — no. 174, 134, 124? 124 ends in 4? No, 124 ends in 4? 124 → yes, ends in 4. 174, 134, 124 → three
- 6: 146, 174? 174 ends in 4 — no. 146, 166 → two
- 8: 178, 182? 182 ends in 2 — only 178

So: 0:2, 2:2, 4:3, 6:2, 8:1 — no pattern.

Wait — perhaps Q1 and Q2 are **complementary in some way**?

Total numbers: 10 in each.

Q2: all primes between 100 and 200? No — missing many.

